<item>
            <title>[SPARK-23267] Increase spark.sql.codegen.hugeMethodLimit to 65535</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23267</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Still saw the performance regression introduced by `spark.sql.codegen.hugeMethodLimit` in our internal workloads. There are two major issues in the current solution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The size of the complied byte code is not identical to the bytecode size of the method. The detection is still not accurate.&#160;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The bytecode size of a single operator (e.g., `SerializeFromObject`) could still exceed 8K limit. We saw the performance regression in such scenario.&#160;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Since it is close to the release of 2.3,&#160;we decide to increase it to 64K for avoiding&#160;the perf regression.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
